{
  "stem": "18470.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 307.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, oh sure, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Many [BACKROUND NOISE] of them went to Dachau, which is the concentration camp that most of them went to, the very first time around.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this is-- this is really a very serious matter-- that incident.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had forgotten it for many years.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then one day I was preparing a talk, which was on my inauguration as president of the college.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had shown the talk to my son.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said, you know, this is a nice talk.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there's nothing of you in here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Can't you-- don't you remember anything that motivated you?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then suddenly a memory came back to me of the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then I pieced it together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because it started the night before, and there was beating on our doors, and windows, and no one actually entering the house.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But it was a very frightening thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It woke me up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then the following morning-- we all then slept together in the living room.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Following morning, my grandfather took me down to the [NON-ENGLISH], which is the place where the town gate had been originally and where the synagogue was located.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there was a brook in front of the synagogue at the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in the brook there was floating fragments of the prayer books and the Torah scrolls, hacked to pieces.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then we went inside the synagogue, which was completely tarred black.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now many of the synagogues were destroyed at Kristallnacht through burning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This synagogue, they couldn't burn because it was a triplex house, with non-Jews living on either side.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So you couldn't burn just the synagogue, so they defaced the synagogue, tore it apart inside.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
